The paper presents a formalism for multi-agent systems, where agents reason and act in a shared environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions a high-level Action Description Language, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper further discusses coordination among agents, which suggests that it may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions a prototype implementation developed in SICStus Prolog, which suggests that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
